OpenSim::SimbodyEngine01_05

SimbodyEngine01_05 Class Reference

#include <SimbodyEngine01_05.h>

Inheritance diagram for SimbodyEngine01_05:

List of all members.

Detailed Description

A wrapper class to use the SimTK Simbody dynamics engine as the underlying engine for OpenSim.

Authors:
Frank C. Anderson
Version:
1.0

Member Data Documentation

AbstractBody* _groundBody [protected]

Body used for ground, the inertial frame.

SimTK::MultibodySystem* _system [protected]

Multibody system.

SimTK::SimbodyMatterSubsystem* _matter [protected]

Matter subsystem.

SimTK::State* _s [protected]

Uniform gravity subsystem.

User-force subsystem. States of the Simbody model. At a minimum, it contains the generalized coordinates (q) and generalized speeds (u).

SimTK::Vector_<SimTK::SpatialVec> _bodyForces [protected]

Vector of spatial vectors containing the accumulated forces and torques that are to be applied to each of the bodies in the matter subsystem.

Forces and torques are accumulated in this vector when the applyForce()/applyTorque() methods are called.

SimTK::Vector _mobilityForces [protected]

Vector of mobility forces containing the accumulated generalized coordinates that are to be applied to the matter subsystem.

The forces are accumulated in this vector when the applyGeneralizedForce() methods are called.
